Phantom has detected the following endpoints running MacOS High Sierra:
{1}

At 10:38am on 2017-11-28 it was publicly announced that in High Sierra the root user account can be enabled by trying to authenticate with any password. This is remotely exploitable if Apple Remote Desktop is enabled and listening on port 5900.

To see additional context and run response actions use Mission Control within Phantom to access the Event with ID {0}

Apple Security Update 2017-001 has been released to fix this vulnerability and should be installed as soon as possible.
